<dl id="n51148f"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n51" href="#n51148f">N51 (VI.B.44)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n51all.htm#n51148f"> 148(f)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> v school of / grimace <small>Orange</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">He <font color="green">[Ashbury]</font> and his son-in-law, Thomas Elrington, established the peculiar Dublin school of playing, noted for its clear, bold elocution, which was for a while overshadowed by Garrick&apos;s <mark>school of grimace</mark> and play of features. <small> Rev. S.C. Hughes, <a name="PVDD" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#PVDD"><cite title="source">The Pre-Victorian Drama in Dublin</cite></a> (1904) 4</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: Transferred to <a name="n51149a" href="n51all.htm#n51149a">N51 (VI.B.44):149(a)</a> </mm> </dd></dl>
